# shadcn/ui — Project UI Standard

Always use shadcn/ui components for UI. Do not create custom implementations of components that shadcn/ui already provides (buttons, dialogs, cards, inputs, dropdowns, etc.). Check the shadcn/ui registry before building anything from scratch.

## Adding Components

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add <component>
```

Multiple at once:

```bash
npx shadcn@latest add button card dialog
```

## Importing Components

Components live in `src/components/ui/` and are imported via the path alias:

```tsx
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
```

## Project Stack

- Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4
- `@/*` alias maps to `./src/*`
- No `tailwind.config.js` — theme config lives in CSS via `@theme` in `globals.css`
- Colors use OKLCH format, not HSL
